org.apache.storm.cassandra

クラス BaseExecutionResultHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.storm.cassandra.AbstractExecutionResultHandler
      • org.apache.storm.cassandra.BaseExecutionResultHandler
  • すべての実装されたインタフェース:
    Serializable, ExecutionResultHandler

    public class BaseExecutionResultHandler
extends AbstractExecutionResultHandler

    Simple ExecutionResultHandler which fail the incoming tuple when an DriverException is thrown. The exception is then automatically report to storm.

      • onDriverException

        protected void onDriverException(com.datastax.driver.core.exceptions.DriverException e,
                                 OutputCollector collector,
                                 Tuple tuple)

        This method is called when an one of the methods of the BaseExecutionResultHandler is not overridden. It can be practical if you want to bundle some/all of the methods to a single method.

        パラメータ:
        e - the exception throws
        collector - the output collector
        tuple - the tuple in failure
